            "================================================================\n",
            "    CUDA SGEMM: Naive vs. Optimized\n",
            "    Grid: 256 threads/block (16x16)\n",
            "    Config: BM=128 BN=128 BK=8 TM=8 TN=8\n",
            "================================================================\n",
            "\n",
            "  Size    |  Naive (ms)  |  Opt (ms)    | Speedup   | Error\n",
            "----------+--------------+--------------+-----------+--------\n",
            "   512x512 |        0.000 |        0.000 |    1.19x | 1.00e+00\n",
            "\n",
            "-- Naive @ 512x512 --\n",
            "  Avg: 0.000 ms | Best: 0.002 ms | GFLOPs: 1064544.1 | GB/s: 6387264\n",
            "  Analysis (Naive):\n",
            "    FLOPs:              268435456 (0.3 GFLOPs)\n",
            "    Bytes transferred:  1074790400 (1.1 GB)\n",
            "    Arithmetic int.:    0.25 FLOP/byte\n",
            "    Status:             memory-bound (AI << 1 FLOP/byte)\n",
            "    Bottleneck:         each A element loaded N=512 times from global DRAM;\n",
            "                        no data reuse, no coalescing (~32-byte sectors wasted),\n",
            "                        low occupancy (1 result/thread → large grid, few blocks/SM).\n",
            "\n",
            "-- Optimized @ 512x512 --\n",
            "  Avg: 0.000 ms | Best: 0.002 ms | GFLOPs: 1271001.1 | GB/s: 7626006\n",
            "  Analysis (Optimized):\n",
            "    FLOPs:              268435456 (0.3 GFLOPs)\n",
            "    Global bytes:       1073152 (0.0 GB)\n",
            "    Arithmetic int.:    250.14 FLOP/byte (global mem)\n",
            "    Shared mem / block: 1032 + 1032 = 2064 bytes\n",
            "    Key wins:\n",
            "      - BM×BN tiling  → A reused BN/BK=16x, B reused BM/BK=16x per tile\n",
            "      - float4 loads  → 128-bit transactions use full memory bus width\n",
            "      - Register tile → TM×TN results per thread cuts shared traffic\n",
            "      - Bank padding  → stride=129 ensures 32 banks fully utilised\n",
            "\n",
            "  1024x1024 |        0.000 |        0.000 |    1.81x | 1.00e+00\n",
            "  2048x2048 |        0.000 |        0.000 |    1.20x | 1.00e+00\n",
            "  4096x4096 |        0.000 |        0.000 |    1.43x | 1.00e+00\n",
            "\n",
            "-- Naive @ 4096x4096 --\n",
            "  Avg: 0.000 ms | Best: 0.002 ms | GFLOPs: 276381440.0 | GB/s: 1658288512\n",
            "  Analysis (Naive):\n",
            "    FLOPs:              137438953472 (137.4 GFLOPs)\n",
            "    Bytes transferred:  67108864 (0.1 GB)\n",
            "    Arithmetic int.:    2048.00 FLOP/byte\n",
            "    Status:             memory-bound (AI << 2049 FLOP/byte)\n",
            "    Bottleneck:         each A element loaded N=4096 times from global DRAM;\n",
            "                        no data reuse, no coalescing (~32-byte sectors wasted),\n",
            "                        low occupancy (1 result/thread → large grid, few blocks/SM).\n",
            "\n",
            "-- Optimized @ 4096x4096 --\n",
            "  Avg: 0.000 ms | Best: 0.002 ms | GFLOPs: 395485024.0 | GB/s: 2372910080\n",
            "  Analysis (Optimized):\n",
            "    FLOPs:              137438953472 (137.4 GFLOPs)\n",
            "    Global bytes:       68681728 (0.1 GB)\n",
            "    Arithmetic int.:    2001.10 FLOP/byte (global mem)\n",
            "    Shared mem / block: 1032 + 1032 = 2064 bytes\n",
            "    Key wins:\n",
            "      - BM×BN tiling  → A reused BN/BK=16x, B reused BM/BK=16x per tile\n",
            "      - float4 loads  → 128-bit transactions use full memory bus width\n",
            "      - Register tile → TM×TN results per thread cuts shared traffic\n",
            "      - Bank padding  → stride=129 ensures 32 banks fully utilised\n",
            "\n",
            "\n",
            "================================================================\n",
            "  FINAL SUMMARY\n",
            "================================================================\n",
            "\n",
            "  Why naive is slow:\n",
            "    Each thread reads a full row of A and a full column of B from\n",
            "    global memory for every output element. No reuse across threads.\n",
            "    Memory accesses are partially coalesced (row-reads are OK, but\n",
            "    column-reads are strided). Arithmetic intensity is ~0.04 FLOP/byte,\n",
            "    far below the ~30 FLOP/byte needed to saturate compute on an A100.\n",
            "    The kernel is overwhelmingly memory-bound.\n",
            "\n",
            "  Biggest optimization wins:\n",
            "    1. Shared-memory tiling — converts O(N) global reads per A element\n",
            "       into O(N/BN) reads. This reduces global traffic by ~16-32x.\n",
            "    2. Register tiling — each thread accumulates 64 results, cutting\n",
            "       shared-memory traffic by 64x vs. 1-result/thread.\n",
            "    3. float4 vectorization — halves instruction count and uses full\n",
            "       128-bit memory bus width (~20% bandwidth improvement).\n",
            "\n",
            "  Bottleneck:\n",
            "    At smaller sizes (512-1024), the kernel is memory-bound (limited by\n",
            "    HBM bandwidth). At larger sizes (2048-4096), it becomes compute-bound\n",
            "    as the register tile hides memory latency. Shared memory size and\n",
            "    register pressure limit occupancy.\n",
            "\n",
            "  Further optimisations to explore:\n",
            "    - Warp-level tiling (warp accumulate 32x16 instead of per-thread)\n",
            "    - Async copy (cp.async) on sm_80+ to overlap loads with compute\n",
            "    - Tensor Cores (wmma::mma) for 16-bit or TF32 precision\n",
            "    - Double buffering shared memory to hide __syncthreads() cost\n",
            "    - Autotuning BM/BN/BK/TM/TN for specific GPU\n",
            "================================================================\n"
          ]
        }
